# Uniform Continuity

Uniform continuity refers to a more stringent criteria of continuity in which one value of $\delta$ is sufficient for all $\epsilon$.
That is, for all $\epsilon > 0$, $\exists\delta > 0$ such that for all $p, q \in X$,
$$ d_X(p, q) < \delta \Rightarrow d_Y(f(p), \:f(q)) < \epsilon. $$

</section>

